{
  "doc_id": "15791",
  "text": "We furthermore found that the expressions given for σ app in [CITATION_1] are in fact analytically identical to the one of Winther and Alder [CITATION_2] (see Appendix). Since for all experimental cross sections listed in table 1 and shown in figure  1 the semi-classical theory of Winther and Alder was employed during the analysis of the data, the σ app results must be identical to the original results σ exp provided the proper input parameters are used. This conclusion is in fact supported by an earlier work of Bertulani et al. [CITATION_3] where it is shown in figure 3 (curve RR) that for the case of an E2 excitation the cross section determined within the Winther and Alder theory deviates by less than 5% from the exact treatment for beam energies above 30 MeV/u.",
